				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drmagnus" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(318209); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=318209&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610252577" alt="DrMagnus" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=318209)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drmagnus" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(318209); return false;" >DrMagnus</a></span> <span class="odate time_1497903217 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">19 Jun 2017 20:13</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2873515">
									

<p>This is earning one of my few no-votes, and it's hard to put in to words why.</p>
<p>I don't dislike this, but this series doesn't appeal to me very much, and as I see more and more entries, they tend to be escalating, while at the same time not expanding very much.</p>
<p>I think if I had more attachment to the characters, I would be more in to this, but I can only really view this from the writing perspective, and I didn't get much of a dimension on Jude or Alexander here. Just one dimensional slugfest with powers, and what flirtations with depth happened were cursory.</p>
<p>All of that being rambled, this is good work, and deserves recognition for that. It's just not my taste.</p>

							</div>

								
					
