			<div class="content" id="post-content-2876400">
									

<p>Isn't writing that doesn't make you grow more attached just another aspect of bad writing? If the first two chapters of a novel don't hook you, then it's bad writing, even if it's not grammatically and technically flawed.</p>
<p>If there were more dimension to it, wouldn't you be more likely for you to form an attachment than you would if the kept acting like straw men? That is just my idea of how it works.</p>

